Pleas held at Pickering on Monday‚ 13 March, 1335, Η before Richard de Willoughby and John de Hambury.

The Sheriff was ordered to summon the above-named to appear this day before the JusticeS, to satisfy the Earl for their fines, for poaching in the forest, of which they were convicted before the Justices by the evidence of the foresters, verderers, and other Officers. They do not appear, and the Sheriff returns that they are not to be found and have nothing in his bailiwick by means of which they can be attached. He is therefore ordered to seize them and keep them safely, so that he can produce them before the Justices on Monday‚ 15 May,
